description: This file contains implementation of the basic container object functions for the Http Ato FxCat2 object, including creation, removal, enrollment, and initialization functions, specific to the HTTP protocol implementation in a BroadWay System environment.

classes.name: HTTP_ATO_FXCAT2_OBJECT
classes.description: The primary object representing the HTTP Ato FxCat2 instance, containing function pointers and OID information for object management.

methods.name: ANSC_HANDLE HttpAtoFxCat2Create(ANSC_HANDLE hContainerContext,ANSC_HANDLE hOwnerContext,ANSC_HANDLE hAnscReserved)
methods.description: Constructs the Http Ato FxCat2 Object, allocates memory, initializes base object fields, and sets up method pointers.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS HttpAtoFxCat2Remove(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject)
methods.description: Destroys the object, freeing associated resources.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS HttpAtoFxCat2EnrollObjects(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject)
methods.description: Enrolls all required subordinate objects for this object.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS HttpAtoFxCat2Initialize(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject)
methods.description: Initializes the object, including base class initialization and setting member function pointers for specific behavior.
